"""A guide to connect local repo to Github"""

At the top of your repository on GitHub.com's Quick Setup page, click "HTTPS/SSH button" to copy the remote repository URL.

In terminal/CLI, add the copied URL for the remote repository where your local repository will be pushed.
 
  > git remote add origin <REMOTE_URL>
  // Sets the new remote
  
  > git remote -v
  // Verifies the new remote URL
  
Push the changes in your local repository to GitHub.com
  > git push origin <remote branch name>
